This paper discusses various privacy notions and their relations, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with privacy and differential privacy. The paper also involves concepts from machine learning and information theory, which suggest "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.IT" (Information Theory) as possible sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the scalability of distributions, which is relevant to "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) and "cs.DB" (Databases) sub-categories.
